<subSubSection id="8BA0523A390DEB84C92BDC8B1DED8234" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="33BDF4D71ED9127A68B5A7993D55F90F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="94C7E64F174EC62E818599C5C9026A3A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The type of 
<taxonomicName id="13B37759969AAE4A1DE8C06BF1365ED3" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="praecox">
<emphasis id="72E1EFE2531FCBA78142BD146144C1F1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea praecox</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is leafless. It also differs from 
<taxonomicName id="A6E94162BC90786015D54F281800E666" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="argentifolia">
<emphasis id="E2319A651D25EECC6B9C27A4761AB196" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea argentifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the smaller suborbicular, upwardly glabrous sepals.
</paragraph>
